BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:-dgE-51h8ZEyqJPxWFQkz
SUMMARY:Free First Thursday: Seattle Art Museum
DTSTAMP:20260205T082835Z
DTSTART:20260205T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Call your friends and bring the family\, admission is FREE to e
	veryone at the Seattle Art Museum on the first Thursday of every month. In
	 addition to our regular hours\, Seattle Art Museum will be open for Free 
	First Thursday evenings from 5-8 pm to provide more opportunities to visit
	 the galleries for free! Evening hours will feature extra activities like 
	live music\, drop-in art making\, and in-gallery experiences for visitors.
	 Tickets are available both onsite and online. 11:30 am\, 1:30 pm\, 6 pm |
	 Public Tour: Highlights from SAM's Collection These 60-minute tours meet 
	at the top of the 3rd floor escalators. 5-8 pm | Art Activity with A Resti
	ng Place Location TBD Samantha Yun Wall: What We Leave Behind invites us t
	o reflect on loss and remembrance. Respond to prompts that encourage conne
	ction\, collaboration\, and healing. A Resting Place \\(ARP\\) is a grief 
	& loss cultural resource center located in Seattle's Chinatown Internation
	al District. 5-8 pm | Darrius Willrich and Band Brotman Forum Join us for 
	a jazz/R&B performance from Darrius Willrich. Darrius is a singer\, songwr
	iter\, pianist\, and educator from Seattle\, WA. He is currently the keybo
	ard player for Digable Planets. He is a featured vocalist on Wiz Khalifa's
	 "Rolling Papers 2" and produced South African rapper Nasty C's song Overp
	riced Steak along with Jake One and Sam Wish. 5-8 pm | Drop-In Build-a-Bea
	st Printmaking Workshop with Brian Lane South Hall Use pre-cut printing bl
	ocks to create your own creature inspired by A Room for Animal Intelligenc
	e on the 4th floor. What story will your imaginary animal tell? 5:30-6:30 
	pm | SAM Gallery Artist Talk SAM Gallery 6:30-7 pm | Artist Talk: Samantha
	 Yun Wall Arnold Board Room Hear from Betty Bowen award winner Samantha Yu
	n Wall on the public opening of her exhibition Samantha Yun Wall: What We 
	Leave Behind. Free First Thursday Evenings Presented by\n\nFrom SEAtoday -
	 Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-first-thursday-seatt
	le-art-museum/16949693/2026-02-05T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT10H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Dyxxhm2B9YzOVz4BOWq27
SUMMARY:Anila Quayyum Agha: Geometry of Light
DTSTAMP:20260205T082835Z
DTSTART:20260205T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Anila Quayyum Agha: Geometry of Light invites you to become par
	t of the art. Agha\, a Pakistani American artist\, animates spaces with he
	r large-scale sculptural installations. Suspended from the ceiling\, Agha’
	s steel cubes are laser-cut with intricate designs that project geometric 
	shadows onto the visitor. She draws on both the light and dark of her own 
	life\, using South Asian art practices to convey the gender discrimination
	 she faced growing up as a young girl in Pakistan. An in-depth exploration
	 of Islamic architecture\, art\, and identity\, this is the first solo exh
	ibition of a Pakistani American artist in SAM’s 90-year history. Agha is c
	arving a name out for herself in the art world—visit the Seattle Asian Art
	 Museum for an immersive and illuminating experience.\n\nFrom SEAtoday - A
	rts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/anila-quayyum-agha-geomet
	ry-of-light/16795597/2026-02-05T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
