BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3g2yuDY1G9EYYiiG6KWXt
SUMMARY:Songs of Black Folk Film Screening
DTSTAMP:20260205T082835Z
DTSTART:20260207T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Black History Month with MOPOP’s Songs of Black Folk 
	Screening   February 7 | Sound \\+ Vision Theater | 11:00 AM  MOPOP is thr
	illed to present a special screening of Songs of Black Folk in celebration
	 of Black History Month this February. Included with museum admission\, th
	e short film follows musical director Ramón Bryant Braxton as he prepares 
	a Juneteenth celebration featuring the largest gathering of Black musical 
	talent on a single PNW stage.  Join us next month in Sound \\+ Vision Thea
	ter for this powerful story of music\, legacy\, and community.  Screening 
	is free with museum ticket.\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/songs-of-black-folk-film-
	screening/18026225/2026-02-07T00
LOCATION:Museum of Pop Culture\, 325 5th Avenue N\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
