BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:9xmcORxcaWSo0VSH7FRwM
SUMMARY:Hill Talk: Blu Dot
DTSTAMP:20260205T082836Z
DTSTART:20260219T000000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description   Event Details Date: Wednesday\, February 18 Time:
	 4:00-6:00 PM Location: Blu Dot Seattle \\(Capitol Hill\\) -  FREE Hill Ta
	lk is about gathering with intention-bringing people together in inspiring
	 and unique GSBA member spaces to connect\, share ideas\, and build relati
	onships rooted in our community. Join us at Blu Dot Seattle for an early e
	vening of conversation\, connection\, and great food. Whether you're recon
	necting with familiar faces or meeting new ones\, Hill Talk is designed to
	 feel easy\, welcoming\, and genuinely human.  Hosted by Alison Scott\, GS
	BA: Capitol Hill\, and Blu Dot with catering by Imperia Lake Union.       
	 About Blu Dot Seattle Located in the historic Colman Auto Building in the
	 heart of \\(well-caffeinated\\) Capitol Hill\, Blu Dot Seattle's 5\,800 s
	quare-foot\, timber-framed space highlights new furniture designs and best
	sellers alike. The showroom is home to a site-specific collage that includ
	es early sketches of products\, images of prototypes\, and references to t
	he things that inspire Blu Dot-music\, architecture\, art\, everyday objec
	ts\, and more. Come in and see what you see. Or sit. They are down with th
	at too. website    About Imperia Lake Union Imperia Lake Union is an inclu
	sive catering company\, florist\, and luxury event venue. Originally built
	 in 1927 and converted to an event venue over 20 years ago\, this 6\,000 s
	quare foot private space overlooks Lake Union from Seattle's Eastlake neig
	hborhood. Imperia features 10-foot chandeliers\, copper ceilings\, a built
	-in dance floor\, gourmet menus\, premium florals\, and an incredible team
	. With an Old Hollywood glamor vibe and a rumored history as a prohibition
	-era speakeasy\, you'll feel transported into living history and classic e
	legance-now brought to Hill Talk through their catering. website\n\nFrom S
	EAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/hill-talk-blu-dot/1777041
	9/2026-02-18T00
LOCATION:Blu Dot\, 401 E Pine St\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:9wei4bAoggSU3GpmzFd3B
SUMMARY:Fuse a Glass Dish (2 part series!)
DTSTAMP:20260205T082836Z
DTSTART:20260219T000000Z
DESCRIPTION:This is a 2 part series! We're firing up the glass kiln for fus
	ing glass\, and this time\, we're using slumping molds to make dishes!  In
	 the first session\, participants will each prepare a glass base. In the 2
	nd session you'll return to fit your base into the dish molds for slumping
	. The second session will be much quicker than the first at about 15 mins 
	or less. We will learn basic glass cutting and preparation and demonstrate
	 a few techniques \\(each participant can choose which to use - or mix the
	m together!\\).\n\nWe've allotted 2 sessions for this workshop: the first 
	on Wednesday February 11th and the 2nd exactly one week later on February 
	18th. You're welcome to return to the makerspace anytime between sessions 
	to fit your glass into its mold. We will do the 2nd kiln firing during the
	 second session or sooner if all pieces have been fitted into their mold. 
	One registration covers both dates.\n\n \n\nPrerequisite: Maker Orientatio
	n\n\nThis session fulfills the training requirements for Glass Tools and p
	rocesses.\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/fuse-a-glass-dish-2-part-
	series/17717261/2026-02-18T00
LOCATION:Billodue Makerspace\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
